Atlantic Fuels Marketing Corp saidtoday it will raise the posted cargo prices for high sulphurfuels in New York Harbor 50 to 75 cts per barrel, effectiveApril two.    The increase brings the prices for two pct sulphur to 19.25dlrs, up 50 cts, 2.2 pct sulphur to 18.75 dlrs, up 50 cts, 2.5pct sulphur to 18.50 dlrs, up 50 cts, 2.8 pct sulphur to 18.25dlrs, up 75 cts, the company said.    Posted prices for 0.3 pct and one pct low sulphur fuelswere unchanged at 22 and 20 dlrs, it said. Reuter&#3;